(72, 10, '(Another) 900 Game in Macedonia', '<p><a href=\"/players/3454\"><strong>Ethan Taylor</strong></a> rolled the 2nd 900 game of the season at the Macedonia store on Wednesday night. It\'s Ethan\'s first season playing in Macedonia, after switching over from the Copley store.</p>\r\n<p>We\'re now up to six 900 games in Skeeball World Tour history! Nice rollin\' Ethan!</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"border: 0;\" src=\"/images/Ethan_Taylor_900.jpeg\" alt=\"Ethan Taylor\'s 900 Game\" width=\"600\" height=\"902\" /></p>', '2018-10-30', 1),
(73, 10, 'Free Skeeball Night', '<p>Machines will be on FREE PLAY from 6:30pm till closing at the following stores:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Brunswick - Monday (November 12th)</li>\r\n<li>Brunswick - Wednesday (November 14th)</li>\r\n<li>Copley - Wednesday (November 14th)</li>\r\n<li>Lakewood - Thursday (November 15th)</li>\r\n<li>Macedonia - Wednesday (November 14th)</li>\r\n<li>Mentor - Tuesday (November 13th)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>All are welcome to play... friends, family and fellow skeeball enthusiasts. So, practice up for the November 17th tournament!</p>', '2018-11-08', 1),
(74, 10, 'Final Tournament Rankings', '<p>The season is now over and the <a href=\"/qualifiers\"><strong>TOURNAMENT RANKINGS</strong></a> have been set as \'Final\'. Teams that told us they aren\'t coming to the  tournament are not included in the rankings. If you see any errors or  ommisions in the rankings, please let us know.</p>\r\n<p>The November 17th tournament is right around the corner. More info will be posted about the tournament later today.</p>\r\n<p>Also, the printable PDF <a title=\"Tournament Bracket (Fall-2018)\" href=\"/pdf/Tournament_Bracket_Online(2018_Fall).pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>TOURNAMENT BRACKET</strong></a> is now available. Please let us know ASAP if something looks incorrect.</p>', '2018-11-12', 1),
(75, 10, 'Fall Skeeball Tournament', '<p>The <strong>2018 Fall Skeeball Tournament</strong> will be held Saturday (November 17th) at the Winking Lizard Party Center (<a href=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?q=25200+Miles+Rd,+Bedford,+Ohio+44146-1322\">25200 Miles Rd, Bedford Heights</a>). Doors open at 5:00pm and matches start at 6:00pm.</p>\r\n<p>Everyone who played in the league (plus their significant other or a    friend) is welcome to attend... even if you didn\'t qualify to  partipate  in  the tournament, though you must have played in the league  to  qualify  to win prizes. Skeeball World Tour is a 21 and older  league...  as is this tournament.</p>\r\n<p>There will be a great complimentary All-You-Can-Eat Buffet, the main   tournament, the Second Chance Bracket, a huge Raffle and a guaranteed   great time!</p>\r\n<p>We will be giving away <strong>$800.00 in Amazon Gift Cards</strong> throughout the evening. You must have played at least 1 week during  this season to qualify and <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>you must be present to win!</strong></span> Here is the schedule of the  gift card drawings:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\r\n<li>7:15pm drawing for a $100 Amazon Gift Card</li>\r\n<li>8:15pm drawing for a $200 Amazon Gift Card</li>\r\n<li>9:15pm drawing for a $500 Amazon Gift Card</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The Winners of the tournament will receive \'3\' $50 Amazon Gift Cards,   while the runners up will receive \'3\' $25 Amazon Gift Cards.</p>\r\n<p>The <strong>Second Chance Bracket</strong> is back! If your team    loses in the first round of the main tournament, you can signup to keep    playing in the Second Chance Bracket. 7:15pm is the deadline to  signup.   The winners of the second chance bracket will receive \'3\' $25  Lizard   Loot Cards.</p>', '2018-11-12', 1),
(76, 10, 'Fall 2018 Tournament Results', '<p>Twelve was the lucky number for the <a href=\"/teams/579\"><strong>Whiskee Shots</strong></a> in Saturday night\'s Fall Skeeball Tournament. The #12 ranked Whiskee Shots showed up with their A-game... knocking off the #1 ranked <a href=\"/teams/777\"><strong>UnbeSKEEvable</strong></a> in the final four, before beating #2 ranked <a href=\"/teams/706\"><strong>Miami Skeat</strong></a> in the finals. This season\'s final was a nail biter and wasn\'t an easy road for the eventual champs. Up 3 games to 2, it looked like they\'d win in 6 games... but <strong>Miami Skeats</strong>\' anchor had other thoughts. Needing a 540 to send the match to a 7th game, <a href=\"..//players/950\">Rick Miller</a> rolled a cool 630 to keep his team alive. Game 7 provided an even greater challenge. Rick\'s turn came up with him needing an 810 in the final game of the night the salvage the championship. He nailed 5 of his first 6 in the 100 hole, giving his team hope that an 810 was possible... but missed on his final 3 balls. This was the 3rd time <strong>Miami Skeat</strong> has made it to the finals, but had to settled for runner-up honors each time. As for the <strong>Whiskee Shots</strong>, <strong><a href=\"..//players/3300\">Brian McPherran</a>,&nbsp;</strong><a href=\"..//players/2138\"><strong>Lindsey Borstein</strong></a> and <a href=\"..//players/2139\"><strong>Josh Borstein</strong></a> (left to right in the picture below) each played great all night and capitalized on it in their first ever trip to the finals.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"border: 0;\" src=\"/images/2018_Fall_Champions.jpg\" alt=\"Whiskee Shots - Fall 2018 Champions\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" /></p>\r\n<p>Last season\'s champions, <strong><a href=\"/teams/760\">Scoopskee Potatoes</a></strong>, were relegated to the <strong>Second Chance Bracket</strong> this season (after losing in the first round). But, they did prevail in at least taking home the less distinguished title this time around... knocking off <strong><a href=\"/teams/835\">Skee U Next Wednesday</a></strong> with a 3-game sweep in the final.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"border: 0;\" src=\"/images/2018_Fall_Second_Chance.jpg\" alt=\"Scoopskee Potatoes (Second Chance Winners)\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Raffle Prize Winners</strong> ($100, $200 and $500 Amazon Gift Cards) are shown below (left to right): <strong><a href=\"..//players/2983\">Rena Grida</a> </strong> (Copley), <a href=\"..//players/1334\"><strong>Ed Zukowski</strong></a> (Copley) and <a href=\"..//players/826\"><strong>Chuck Lewis</strong></a> (Macedonia). An interesting side note about this year\'s $500 Amazon Gift Card winner... Chuck Lewis also won the top prize at the Fall Tournament in 2017.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"border: 0;\" src=\"/images/2018_Fall_100_Winner.jpg\" alt=\"Rena Grida - $100 Gift Card Winner\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" />&nbsp;<img style=\"border: 0;\" src=\"/images/2018_Fall_200_Winner.jpg\" alt=\"Ed Zukowski - $200 Gift Card Winner\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /> <img style=\"border: 0;\" src=\"/images/2018_Fall_500_Winner.jpg\" alt=\"Chuck Lewis - $500 Gift Card Winner\" /></p>\r\n<p>As always, <a href=\"https://www.sallazuka.com/Skee-Ball/2018-Fall-Skeeball-Championships\"><strong>Sal\'s Photos</strong></a> of the event are available for viewing.</p>', '2018-11-19', 1),
(77, 10, 'Winter Skeeball Season', '<p>Dates for the Winter Skeeball League are:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: circle;\">\r\n<li>Registration ends: January 10th, 2019</li>\r\n<li>Season starts: January 14th, 2019</li>\r\n<li>Season ends: March 14th, 2019</li>\r\n<li>Tournament: March 23rd, 2019</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Registration will open next week (either December 3rd or 4th) and the link will be posted, so check back soon!</p>\r\n<p>Leagues will be at the following \'Stores (Nights) - Times\':</p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\r\n<li>Brunswick (Monday and Wednesday) - 6:30pm and 7:45pm</li>\r\n<li>Copley (Wednesday) - 6:30pm, 7:45pm and 9:00pm</li>\r\n<li>Lakewood (Thursday) - 7:00pm and 8:30pm</li>\r\n<li>Macedonia (Wednesday) - 7:00pm and 8:30pm</li>\r\n<li>Mentor (Tuesda and Thursday) - 7:00pm and 8:30pm</li>\r\n</ul>', '2018-11-28', 1),
(78, 10, 'New items on this website', '<p>After having it on our to-do list for several seasons, we finally have a list of the <strong><a href=\"/champions\">yearly Skeeball World Tour champions</a></strong> on the website. It\'s on the top navigation bar next to \'Contact Us\'.</p>\r\n<p>Also new is the ability to access your team\'s stats for every year they\'ve played in the league.. just like it has always been available for your player stats.</p>', '2018-12-03', 1),
(79, 10, 'Whiskee Shots\' night to remember, remembered', '<p>For the recently crowned first-time champion <strong><a href=\"/teams/579\">Whiskee Shots</a></strong>, November 17th was a night to remember. Now, thanks to Brian, Lindsey and Josh the rest of us can get a first hand view of what that night was like for them in their quest for the title.</p>\r\n<p>This very well done video speaks for itself:</p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://youtu.be/2NE1ppLCsmw\" target=\"_blank\">https://youtu.be/2NE1ppLCsmw</a></strong></p>', '2018-12-04', 1),
(80, 10, 'Winter Skeeball Season', '<p>Schedules for the new season have been posted... and the new season will be starting on Monday, January 14th.</p>\r\n<p>Please let us know as soon as possible if you see any errors in those \'fresh off the presses\' schedules.</p>\r\n<p>Good luck in the new season!</p>', '2019-01-11', 1),
